feat: add "what happens when you run it?" section + tighten wordmark

Adds RealOutput.tsx — a new homepage section placed between Hero and
Curative Triad. Shows the full pipeline:

  scan → explain → cure → apply → undo

with real terminal output for each verb. The argument is "show, don't
tell": a vertical sequence of five real CLI outputs converts harder
than any WebGL set piece. This section now carries the conceptual
weight; the Curative Triad section that follows explains the mental
model behind it.

Also:
